{"parse":{"title":"Paulo Freire: The Man from Recife","pageid":34391746,"revid":830742377,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"plainlinks metadata ambox ambox-style\" role=\"presentation\"><tbody><tr><td class=\"mbox-image\"><div style=\"width:52px\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/f/f2/Edit-clear.svg/40px-Edit-clear.svg.png\" width=\"40\" height=\"40\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/f/f2/Edit-clear.svg/60px-Edit-clear.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/f/f2/Edit-clear.svg/80px-Edit-clear.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"48\" data-file-height=\"48\" /></div></td><td class=\"mbox-text\"><div class=\"mbox-text-span\">This article <b>reads like a <a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:What_Wikipedia_is_not#SOAPBOX\" title=\"Wikipedia:What Wikipedia is not\">review</a> rather than an encyclopedic description of the subject</b>.<span class=\"hide-when-compact\"> Please help <a class=\"external text\" href=\"//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Paulo_Freire:_The_Man_from_Recife&amp;action=edit\">improve this article</a> to make it <a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Neutral_point_of_view\" title=\"Wikipedia:Neutral point of view\">neutral</a> in tone and meet Wikipedia's <a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Manual_of_Style\" title=\"Wikipedia:Manual of Style\">quality standards</a>.</span>  <small><i>(January 2012)</i></small></div></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<table class=\"infobox vcard\" style=\"width:22em\"><caption style=\"font-style:italic;padding-bottom:0.2em;\">Paulo Freire: The Man from Recife <span class=\"Z3988\" title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Paulo+Freire%3A+The+Man+from+Recife&amp;rft.author=%5B%5BJames+D.+Kirylo%5D%5D&amp;rft.pages=359\"></span></caption><tbody><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;display:none\"><div>First edition cover</div></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Author</th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/James_D._Kirylo\" title=\"James D. Kirylo\">James D. Kirylo</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Country</th><td>\nUnited States</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Language</th><td>\nEnglish</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Genre</th><td>\nacademic</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Published</th><td>\n2011 Peter Lang</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Media&#160;type</th><td>\nPrint (paperback)</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Pages</th><td>\n359</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\"><a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a></th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-1-4331-0878-5\" title=\"Special:BookSources/978-1-4331-0878-5\">978-1-4331-0878-5</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>Paulo Freire: The Man from Recife</b> is a scholarly book written by American author <a href=\"/wiki/James_D._Kirylo\" title=\"James D. Kirylo\">James D. Kirylo</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-lang_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-lang-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> It is a comprehensive text that covers the life, work, and thought of the great Brazilian educator, <a href=\"/wiki/Paulo_Freire\" title=\"Paulo Freire\">Paulo Freire</a> (1921\u20131997), who was born and raised in <a href=\"/wiki/Recife,_Brazil\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Recife, Brazil\">Recife, Brazil</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-lang_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-lang-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> Remarkably grounded in the wisdom of humility, yet gifted with a determined strength, deep insight, and perceptive intelligence, Freire not only believed in the human spirit, goodness, and the fostering of a more hopeful world, but was also profoundly committed to challenge individuals and political, educational, and religious structures that perpetuated the status quo.<sup id=\"cite_ref-lang_2-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-lang-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Of the book, Ana Maria Ara\u00fajo Freire, Paulo\u2019s widow, stated, \u201cIf Paulo Freire could read this book, he would certainly be happy with how James D. Kirylo has presented his thought, faithfully and respectfully recreating him without distortion.\u201d<sup id=\"cite_ref-lang_2-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-lang-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:242px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:2015-04-23_Kirylo_Cope_DSC0072.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/70/2015-04-23_Kirylo_Cope_DSC0072.jpg/240px-2015-04-23_Kirylo_Cope_DSC0072.jpg\" width=\"240\" height=\"140\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/70/2015-04-23_Kirylo_Cope_DSC0072.jpg/360px-2015-04-23_Kirylo_Cope_DSC0072.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/70/2015-04-23_Kirylo_Cope_DSC0072.jpg/480px-2015-04-23_Kirylo_Cope_DSC0072.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"3859\" data-file-height=\"2255\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:2015-04-23_Kirylo_Cope_DSC0072.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Author <a href=\"/wiki/James_D._Kirylo\" title=\"James D. Kirylo\">James D. Kirylo</a>, president of <a href=\"/wiki/Southeastern_Louisiana_University\" title=\"Southeastern Louisiana University\">Southeastern Louisiana University</a>'s <a href=\"/wiki/Academic_senate\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Academic senate\">Faculty Senate</a> confers with Kevin L. Cope, president of the <a href=\"/wiki/LSU\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"LSU\">LSU</a> Faculty Senate and president of the Association of Louisiana Faculty Senates, during a panel presentation in <a href=\"/wiki/Hammond,_Louisiana\" title=\"Hammond, Louisiana\">Hammond</a>, on \"State of (Dis)Repair: Higher Education in Louisiana\" during 2015.</div></div></div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Reviews\">Reviews</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Paulo_Freire:_The_Man_from_Recife&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Reviews\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p><a href=\"/wiki/Donaldo_Macedo\" title=\"Donaldo Macedo\">Donaldo Macedo</a>, author of numerous books and one who significantly collaborated with Paulo, asserted that Kirylo\u2019s \u201cinsightful book is a great complement to Paulo Freire\u2019s <i>Letters to Cristina</i> and Ana Maria Ara\u00fajo Freire\u2019s <i>Paulo Freire: Uma Hist\u00f3ria de Vida</i>\u2026Reading Kirylo\u2019s book reminds me, once again, how I feel enormously blessed for having had the opportunity to work and collaborate with Paulo Freire so closely for many years.\u201d<sup id=\"cite_ref-lang_2-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-lang-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>According to <a href=\"/wiki/Peter_McLaren\" title=\"Peter McLaren\">Peter McLaren</a>, \"Paulo Freire has cultivated the ground for a long revolution, and James D. Kirylo's outstanding new work has skillfully and with prescient insight illuminated this ground in ways few books on Freire have managed to accomplish.\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-lang_2-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-lang-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Paulo_Freire:_The_Man_from_Recife&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.amazon.com/Paulo-Freire-Counterpoints-Postmodern-Education/dp/143310878X/ref=sr_1_1?s=books&amp;ie=UTF8&amp;qid=1384126212&amp;sr=1-1&amp;keywords=james+kirylo\">\"Paulo Freire\"</a>. <i>Amazon.com</i><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">10 November</span> 2013</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=Amazon.com&amp;rft.atitle=Paulo+Freire&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FPaulo-Freire-Counterpoints-Postmodern-Education%2Fdp%2F143310878X%2Fref%3Dsr_1_1%3Fs%3Dbooks%26ie%3DUTF8%26qid%3D1384126212%26sr%3D1-1%26keywords%3Djames%2Bkirylo&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3APaulo+Freire%3A+The+Man+from+Recife\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-lang-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-lang_2-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-lang_2-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-lang_2-2\"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-lang_2-3\"><sup><i><b>d</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-lang_2-4\"><sup><i><b>e</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-lang_2-5\"><sup><i><b>f</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20160303210911/http://www.peterlang.com/index.cfm?event=cmp.ccc.seitenstruktur.detailseiten&amp;seitentyp=produkt&amp;pk=54227&amp;concordeid=310878\">\"Paulo Freire\"</a>. <i>Peter Lang International Academic Publishers</i>. Archived from <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.peterlang.com/index.cfm?event=cmp.ccc.seitenstruktur.detailseiten&amp;seitentyp=produkt&amp;pk=54227&amp;concordeid=310878\">the original</a> on 3 March 2016<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"